properties.name: Surfside Beach
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  Between the cities of Seal Beach and Sunset Beach is the tiny, little community of Surfside. A scenic stretch of coastline on the Pacific Ocean features a post office and 400 to 500 houses. Most hardly know it exists because this little piece of paradise is guard gated. There are no stores, restaurants and scarce visitor parking. It\'s also very popular and very crowded surfer beach. One of the most popular surfing locations in Orange County.
